        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[3px] border-orange-700 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1 (portfolio launch + presentation upgrade):</strong> Website went live with full-screen galleries, before/after sliders, project narratives. Week 1: 18 project inquiries (vs. 8-10 before = 125% increase). Week 2: First $120K custom home project (client: "Your portfolio shows you understand modern design, not just boxes"). Week 3: Portfolio PageSpeed 96 (was 48 = 100% improvement, bounce rate 67%→23%). Week 4: Process page reducing discovery call duration 47% (clients understand timeline before calling). Monthly inquiries: 31 (vs. 10 before = 210% increase). Monthly revenue: $72,000 (vs. $48,000 baseline = 50% increase). <strong>Month 2:</strong> Testimonials driving conversions. Added 12 client testimonials with photos, specific results ("Our home won 2023 NARI Design Award"). Month 2: 34 inquiries, 73% qualified (was 45%). Qualified leads: +62%. Average project size increasing: $64,000 (clients seeing higher-end work). Monthly revenue: $96,000 (vs. $48,000 baseline = 100% increase). <strong>Month 3:</strong> Consistent 28-35 inquiries/month. 3-4 projects booking monthly (was 1-2). Google ranking #1 for "Seattle modern residential architect" (was page 3). Client showing portfolio to spouses: "This architect presents professionally, they'll deliver professionally." Monthly revenue: $112,000 (vs. $48,000 baseline = 133% increase). 3-month total: $280,000 (vs. $144,000 previous 3 months = 94% increase). Presentation = quality perception = revenue growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

